<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Commit Bot</title>
</head>
<body>
    <h1>Commit Bot</h1>
    <form action="/start-commit" method="post">
        <label for="commitCount">Number of Commits:</label>
        <input 
            type="number" 
            id="commitCount" 
            name="commitCount" 
            required 
        /><br/><br/>

        <label for="commitYear">Year for Commits:</label>
        <input 
            type="number" 
            id="commitYear" 
            name="commitYear" 
            required 
        /><br/><br/>

        <label for="username">GitHub Username:</label>
        <input 
            type="text" 
            id="username" 
            name="username" 
            required 
        /><br/><br/>

        <label for="token">GitHub Token:</label>
        <input 
            type="password" 
            id="token" 
            name="token" 
            required 
        /><br/><br/>

        <button type="submit">Start Commits</button>
    </form>

    <div class="help">
        <h2>How to Use the Commit Bot</h2>
        <p>Follow these steps to use the Commit Bot:</p>
        <ol>
            <li>Enter the number of commits you want to generate in the "Number of Commits" field.</li>
            <li>Enter the year for which you want the commits to be made in the "Year for Commits" field.</li>
            <li>Enter your GitHub username in the "GitHub Username" field.</li>
            <li>Generate a GitHub personal access token with the required permissions. See the instructions below for help.</li>
            <li>Enter the generated token in the "GitHub Token" field.</li>
            <li>Click the "Start Commits" button to begin the process.</li>
        </ol>
        <h3>Generating a GitHub Token</h3>
        <p>To generate a GitHub token:</p>
        <ol>
            <li>Go to <a href="https://github.com/settings/tokens" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">GitHub Settings</a>.</li>
            <li>Click on <strong>Generate new token</strong>.</li>
            <li>Select the scopes you need (e.g., <strong>repo</strong> for full control of private repositories).</li>
            <li>Click <strong>Generate token</strong>.</li>
            <li>Copy the generated token and paste it in the "GitHub Token" field.</li>
        </ol>
    </div>
</body>
</html>